<div id='instructions'>
<h1>3 Card Poker</h1>
<div class='body'>
<p>
Welcome to 3 Card Poker! This is a card game that uses a single standard 52-card deck of cards. Like all games on bitZino, our 3 Card Poker is
<a href="/about/fair">Provably Fair</a>.
</p>
<p>3 Card Poker is actually two games in one: the Pairplus game and the Ante game. You can play both games at once, or just choose one.</p>
<p>
<b>Step 1: Place your bets.</b>
You can wager up to 25฿ for both the Pairplus wager and the Ante wager. Bets in each game do not have to be equal.
</p>
<p class='sub'>Note that if you are placing an Ante wager, you must leave at least an equal amount unwagered in order to be able to make the subsequent Raise. For example, if you have 100 mBTC cashed in, you cannot place an Ante wager higher than 50 mBTC. Don't worry though, the game will keep track of the maximum bet size for you!</p>
<p class='sub'>After placing your bets, we will deal three cards to you, and three cards to the dealer.</p>
<p class='sub'>
If you chose not to place an Ante wager, you can skip to
<b>Step 4.</b>
</p>
<p>
<b>Step 2: Raise or Fold</b>
If you Raise, you will move on to the next step. If you Fold, you will lose your Ante wager, and be out of the hand.
</p>
<p class='sub'>
Note that 3 Card Poker uses a different order of poker hands than traditional 5 Card Poker. The order of hands, from best to worst, is as follows:
</p>
<p class='hand_order'>
<div class='payout_row'>Mini Royal</div>
<div class='payout_row'>Straight Flush</div>
<div class='payout_row'>3 of a Kind</div>
<div class='payout_row'>Straight</div>
<div class='payout_row'>Flush</div>
<div class='payout_row'>Pair</div>
<div class='payout_row'>High Card</div>
</p>
<p class='sub'>
Note that a Mini Royal is an Ace, King, Queen all of the same suit.
</p>
<p>
<b>Step 3: Showdown</b>
</p>
<p class='sub'>
<b>If you Raised in Step 2</b>
the dealer will choose to either fold or call. The dealer will always call with a Queen High or better, and always fold with worse.
<ul>
<li>If the dealer folds, then you win your Ante bet but your Raise bet is a push.</li>
<li>If the dealer calls and your hand is better or equal, then you win both your Ante bet and your Raise bet.</li>
<li>If the dealer calls and has a better hand, then you lose both your Ante bet and your Raise bet.</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p class='sub'>
<b>You may also be eligible for the Ante Bonus.</b>
If you have a Straight or better, you win a bonus according to the Ante Bonus pay table - regardless of whether you have a better hand than the dealer!
</p>
<p>
<b>Step 4: Collect your Pairplus winnings</b>
</p>
<p class='sub'>
<b>If you placed a Pairplus wager</b>
and have a pair or better you win according to the Pairplus pay table!
</p>
</div>
